<!doctype html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>About <%=appName%></title>
    <link rel="stylesheet"  type="text/css" href="/main.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1><%=appName%></h1>
    <div class="navbar">
      <a href="list" title="View the list of patients">List patients</a>
      <a href="search" title="Search for a patient">Search for patient</a>
      <a href="addpatient" title="Add a new patient">Add a new patient</a>
      <a href="register" title="Register as a new user">Register new user</a>
      <a href="login" title="Login to your account">Login with us</a>
      <a href="about" title="Learn more about <%=appName%>" class="active">About <%=appName%></a>
      <a href="/logout" title="Logout from your account">Logout</a>
    </div>
    
    <script>
    // Get all navigation links
    const navLinks = document.querySelectorAll('.navbar a');
    
    // Add event listeners to each link
    navLinks.forEach(link => {
      // Show message when hovering over the link
      link.addEventListener('mouseover', function() {
        // Get the message from the link's title attribute
        const message = this.getAttribute('title');
        // Display the message in a tooltip or other UI element
        // For example, you can create a tooltip element and append it to the body
        const tooltip = document.createElement('div');
        tooltip.classList.add('tooltip');
        tooltip.textContent = message;
        // Position the tooltip relative to the link
        const linkRect = this.getBoundingClientRect();
        tooltip.style.top = `${linkRect.top + linkRect.height}px`;
        tooltip.style.left = `${linkRect.left}px`;
        // Append the tooltip to the body
        document.body.appendChild(tooltip);
    
        // Remove the tooltip when mouse leaves the link
        link.addEventListener('mouseleave', function() {
          tooltip.remove();
        });
      });
    });
    </script>
    
    <h2>About <%=appName%></h2>
    <p>Information about app</p>
    <div class="container">
      <h1>About Our App</h1>
      <p>Welcome to <strong><%=appName%></strong>, a cutting-edge medical application designed to revolutionize the way healthcare professionals manage patient data. At <strong><%=appName%></strong>, we're dedicated to providing an intuitive and secure platform for doctors and NHS staff to streamline their workflow and enhance patient care.</p>
      
      <h2>Our Mission</h2>
      <p>Our mission is to empower medical professionals with tools that simplify the process of managing patient records, enabling them to make informed decisions quickly and effectively. With <strong><%=appName%></strong>, doctors can access vital patient information anytime, anywhere, facilitating better healthcare outcomes.</p>
      
      <h2>Key Features</h2>
      <ul>
          <li><strong>Efficient Data Management:</strong> Easily add, save, and share patient records, ensuring comprehensive and up-to-date medical information is readily available.</li>
          <li><strong>Secure Storage:</strong> We prioritize data security, employing robust encryption and authentication measures to safeguard sensitive patient data.</li>
          <li><strong>Intuitive Interface:</strong> Designed with user experience in mind, our platform offers a user-friendly interface that minimizes learning curves and maximizes productivity.</li>
          <li><strong>Advanced Search Functionality:</strong> Quickly locate patient records with powerful search capabilities, allowing medical professionals to retrieve relevant information with ease.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2>Our Commitment</h2>
      <p>At <strong><%=appName%></strong>, we're committed to continuous improvement and innovation. We strive to incorporate user feedback and emerging technologies to evolve our platform and meet the evolving needs of healthcare professionals.</p>
      
      <h2>Get Started Today</h2>
      <p>Join us in revolutionizing patient care. Sign up for <strong><%=appName%></strong> today and experience the future of medical data management.</p>
  </div>
  </body>
</html>